<div class="container mt-4">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col">
			<ul class="list-group">
				<li class="list-group-item active"><strong>Common Name: <%= @plants["common_name"] %></strong></li>
				<li class="list-group-item">Genus: <%= @plants["genus"].nil? ? "Information not available" : @plants["genus"] %></li>
				<li class="list-group-item">Edible parts: <%= @plants["edible_part"].nil? ? "Not pets friendly" : @plants["edible_part"] %></li>
				<li class="list-group-item">Maximum height (in cm): <%= @plants["specifications"]["maximum_height"]["cm"].nil? ? "Information not available" : @plants["specifications"]["maximum_height"]["cm"] %></li>
			</ul>
				<br>
				<p>Have a story about your <%= @plants["common_name"] %>? <%= link_to "Share now", new_plant_path, class: "link" %></p>
		</div>
		<div class="col">
			<p>Calendula (Calendula officinalis) is a short-lived perennial in warmer climates, but it is usually grown as an annual flower in garden beds and containers. The common name of pot marigold derives because the gold flowers that bloomed during the festivals of the Virgin Mary in Renaissance times (mary + gold = marigold) were often used in cooking. Today, gardeners simply grow these plants for their cheery flowers and profuse blooming habit. Though they most commonly are seen in varieties with yellow and orange flowers, there are also more subtle shades of pink and cream available.</p>
		</div>
	</div>
	

<!-- Pictures -->
	<div class="row">
		<% @flowers.each_with_index do |flower, n| %>
		<div class="col">
			<div class="d-flex justify-content-around mt-2">
				<div class="card">
				<img src="<%= flower["image_url"] unless flower["image_url"] == nil %>" id="plant-show-img" class="rounded mx-auto d-block" alt="...">
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>	
	<% end %>
</div>












